Requires:
 Django environment (Python, Web Server (Apache recommended), mod_python (if Apache preferred), Django*)
 Python Imaging Library (PIL)
 BeautifulSoup
 DBMS (MySQL recommended)

* We're using r7046 of Django, so use: svn co http://code.djangoproject.com/svn/django/trunk -r7046
* You need to edit /usr/lib/python2.4/site-packages/django/contrib/auth/views.py in order to make login work properly:
* move the line "request.session.set_test_cookie()" just after "redirect_to = request.REQUEST.get(redirect_field_name, '')"

Setup:
 1. edit settings.py
 2. run 'python manage.py syncdb'
 3. run 'mkdir media/upload/{image,video} -p'
 4. run 'chmod 777 -R media/upload'
 5. copy htaccess file into the web directory as .htaccess and
    edit it.
 6. restart apache and go to WEB_URL/admin
